Hi,

I would like to report what I think to be an issue, return types are not allowed to be specified in 9.5.0:

Declare "void" as the return type causes the compilation to fail.

```
class Test {
	
	private id: number;
	
	public get Id(): number {
		return this.id;
	}
	
	public set Id(id: number): void {
		this.id = id;
	}	
}
```

http://www.typescriptlang.org/Playground/#src=class%20Test%20%7B%0A%09%0A%09private%20id%3A%20number%3B%0A%09%0A%09public%20get%20Id()%3A%20number%20%7B%0A%09%09return%20this.id%3B%0A%09%7D%0A%09%0A%09public%20set%20Id(id%3A%20number)%3A%20void%20%7B%0A%09%09this.id%20%3D%20id%3B%0A%09%7D%09%0A%7D

Thanks in advance,

Carlos Adriano Portes
